@Steve L I would bet that @Lauren does understand the weekly progression of difficulty. People can have opinions on clues irrespective of how easy or difficult it was for them to solve a particular puzzle. I often do. 

@Lauren gives no examples, and I personally thought there was plenty of cleverness in the clues in the puzzle today (very much so), but I agree with the sentiment that late-week clues should be more difficult through clever trickery and misdirection rather than obscurity (though having *some* clues based on more esoteric knowledge seems reasonable) or because the clue doesn‚Äôt match the answer properly - my personal bugaboo.

